        "# CHALLENGE 1: SKEWNESS IN FINANCIAL RETURNS\n",
        "\n",
        "## Definition\n",
        "\n",
        "**Skewness** measures the asymmetry of a return distribution:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$S = \\frac{\\mathbb{E}[(X - \\mu)^3]}{\\sigma^3} = \\frac{\\frac{1}{n}\\sum_{i=1}^n (r_i - \\bar{r})^3}{\\left[\\frac{1}{n}\\sum_{i=1}^n (r_i - \\bar{r})^2\\right]^{3/2}}$$\n",
        "\n",
        "## Interpretation\n",
        "\n",
        "| Skewness Value | Interpretation |\n",
        "|----------------|----------------|\n",
        "| **S < 0** (Negative) | Left tail heavier → More frequent small gains but occasional large losses. Common in financial returns due to crash risk. |\n",
        "| **S > 0** (Positive) | Right tail heavier → More frequent small losses but occasional large gains. |\n",
        "| **S = 0** | Symmetric distribution (rare in financial data). |\n",
        "\n",
