        "# Diagnosing Skewness\n",
        "\n",
        "## Methods to Detect Skewness\n",
        "\n",
        "### 1. Jarque-Bera Normality Test\n",
        "The Jarque-Bera test statistic is calculated as:\n",
        "$$JB = \\frac{n}{6}\\left(S^2 + \\frac{(K-3)^2}{4}\\right)$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Where:\n",
        "- $S$ = skewness\n",
        "- $K$ = kurtosis\n",
        "- $n$ = sample size\n",
        "\n",
        "**Decision Rule**: Reject normality if p-value < 0.05\n",
        "\n",
        "### 2. Rule of Thumb Thresholds\n",
        "- |Skewness| > 1 → Highly skewed distribution\n",
        "- |Skewness| > 0.5 → Moderately skewed distribution\n",
        "- |Skewness| < 0.5 → Approximately symmetric\n",
        "\n",
        "### 3. Mean vs. Median Comparison\n",
        "- In a symmetric distribution: **Mean ≈ Median**\n",
        "- In a right-skewed distribution: **Mean > Median**\n",
        "- In a left-skewed distribution: **Mean < Median**\n",
        "\n",
        "## Solutions to Address Skewness\n",
        "\n",
        "| Method | Description |\n",
        "|--------|-------------|\n",
        "| **EGARCH** | Exponential GARCH - captures asymmetric volatility response to positive vs negative shocks |\n",
        "| **GJR-GARCH** | Glosten-Jagannathan-Runkle model - leverage effects with an indicator variable |\n",
        "| **Cornish-Fisher VaR** | Adjusts VaR calculations for skewness and kurtosis |\n",
        "| **Johnson SU Transformation** | Normalizes skewed data through mathematical transformation |\n",
        "| **Nonparametric Methods** | Historical simulation with longer windows |\n",
        "| **Heavy-tailed Distributions** | Use Student-t or GED for error terms instead of normal |\n",
        "\n"
