        "# CHALLENGE 3: OVERFITTING\n",
        "\n",
        "## Definition\n",
        "\n",
        "**Overfitting** occurs when a model learns random noise instead of the true underlying signal.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Key Concepts\n",
        "\n",
        "**In-Sample Error:**\n",
        "$$MSE_{train} = \\frac{1}{n}\\sum_{i=1}^n (y_i - \\hat{y}_i)^2$$\n",
        "\n",
        "**Out-of-Sample Error:**\n",
        "$$MSE_{test} = \\frac{1}{m}\\sum_{i=1}^m (y_i^* - \\hat{y}_i^*)^2$$\n",
        "\n",
        "**Overfitting is diagnosed when:** $MSE_{test} \\gg MSE_{train}$\n",
        "\n",
        "## The Bias-Variance Tradeoff\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\\text{Expected Prediction Error} = \\text{Bias}^2 + \\text{Variance} + \\text{Irreducible Error}$$\n",
        "\n",
        "| Model Complexity | Bias | Variance | Total Error |\n",
        "|------------------|------|----------|-------------|\n",
        "| Too Simple (Underfit) | High | Low | High |\n",
        "| Just Right | Moderate | Moderate | **Minimum** |\n",
        "| Too Complex (Overfit) | Low | High | High |\n",
        "\n",
        "## Why Overfitting Happens in Volatility Modeling\n",
        "\n",
        "Adding too many lags, exogenous variables, or complex GARCH extensions can capture random patterns that don't replicate out-of-sample, harming:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. **Forecasting performance** - Predictions fail on new data\n",
        "2. **Derivative pricing** - Options are priced incorrectly\n",
        "3. **Risk management** - VaR calculations become unreliable\n",
        "4. **Portfolio optimization** - Capital allocation based on spurious patterns\n",
