        "# Diagnosing Overfitting\n",
        "\n",
        "## Warning Signs of Overfitting\n",
        "\n",
        "| Sign | Description |\n",
        "|------|-------------|\n",
        "| **High R², poor predictions** | Very high in-sample fit but poor out-of-sample performance |\n",
        "| **Large gap in MSE** | Test MSE significantly > training MSE |\n",
        "| **Unstable coefficients** | Adding/removing one observation changes coefficients dramatically |\n",
        "| **Complexity without improvement** | Adding parameters doesn't improve validation metrics |\n",
        "| **Negative adjusted R²** | Indicates predictors are adding noise, not signal |\n",
        "\n",
        "## The Parsimony Principle\n",
        "\n",
        "$$AIC = -2\\ln(\\hat{L}) + 2k$$\n",
        "$$BIC = -2\\ln(\\hat{L}) + k\\ln(n)$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Where:\n",
        "- $\\hat{L}$ = maximized likelihood\n",
        "- $k$ = number of parameters\n",
        "- $n$ = sample size\n",
        "\n",
        "**Lower AIC/BIC indicates better model** (penalizes complexity)\n",
        "\n",
        "## Solutions to Prevent Overfitting\n",
        "\n",
        "| Method | Description |\n",
        "|--------|-------------|\n",
        "| **Cross-Validation** | k-fold or time-series split validation |\n",
        "| **Regularization (Ridge)** | L2 penalty: $\\min \\sum(y_i - \\hat{y}_i)^2 + \\lambda\\sum\\beta_j^2$ |\n",
        "| **Regularization (Lasso)** | L1 penalty: Shrinks some coefficients to zero |\n",
        "| **Elastic Net** | Combines L1 and L2 penalties |\n",
        "| **Information Criteria** | AIC, BIC for model selection |\n",
        "| **Out-of-Sample Testing** | Rolling window validation |\n",
        "| **Bayesian Methods** | Prior distributions provide natural regularization |\n",
        "| **Simpler Models** | Occam's razor - prefer parsimonious models |\n",
        "\n",
        "## Best Practice\n",
        "\n",
        "**Always validate on out-of-sample data** Never trust in-sample performance alone.\n",
        "\n"
