        "# Diagnosing Multicollinearity\n",
        "\n",
        "## Detection Methods\n",
        "\n",
        "### 1. Correlation Matrix\n",
        "- Look for absolute correlation coefficients $|r| > 0.7$ between predictors\n",
        "- High correlations indicate potential multicollinearity\n",
        "\n",
        "### 2. Variance Inflation Factor (VIF)\n",
        "$$VIF_k = \\frac{1}{1 - R_k^2}$$\n",
        "\n",
        "- $VIF_k > 5$ → Problematic\n",
        "- $VIF_k > 10$ → Severe\n",
        "\n",
        "### 3. Coefficient Instability\n",
        "- Small changes in data cause large changes in coefficient estimates\n",
        "- Signs of coefficients may flip with minor data modifications\n",
        "\n",
        "### 4. Eigenvalue Analysis\n",
        "- Small eigenvalues of $X^TX$ indicate multicollinearity\n",
        "- Condition number > 30 suggests serious multicollinearity\n",
        "\n",
        "## Solutions to Fix Multicollinearity\n",
        "\n",
        "| Method | Description |\n",
        "|--------|-------------|\n",
        "| **PCA (Principal Component Analysis)** | Create orthogonal (uncorrelated) factors |\n",
        "| **Ridge Regression (L2)** | $\\min \\sum(y_i - \\hat{y}_i)^2 + \\lambda\\sum\\beta_j^2$ |\n",
        "| **Lasso Regression (L1)** | Automatically selects features, drops correlated ones |\n",
        "| **Drop Redundant Variables** | Keep SMA_5, drop SMA_10 (domain knowledge) |\n",
        "| **Partial Least Squares (PLS)** | Finds components that explain both predictors and response |\n",
        "| **Increase Sample Size** | More observations can reduce correlation issues |\n",
        "| **Variable Transformation** | Use ratios or differences instead of levels |\n",
        "\n",
        "## Ridge vs. Lasso Regularization\n",
        "\n",
        "| Method | Penalty | Effect |\n",
        "|--------|---------|--------|\n",
        "| **Ridge** | $\\lambda\\sum\\beta_j^2$ | Shrinks coefficients toward zero, keeps all predictors |\n",
        "| **Lasso** | $\\lambda\\sum|\\beta_j|$ | Can shrink coefficients exactly to zero (feature selection) |\n",
        "| **Elastic Net** | Combines both | Best of both worlds |\n",
        "\n",
        "## Best Practice\n",
        "\n",
        "**Always check VIF before interpreting regression coefficients!**\n"
